timber line
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:the highest limit of (timber-)tree growth (cf. bush-, snow-, etc. line)
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: aka timber-line; ca1900 at least ca1952 Busdriver, Routeburn, Otago  `The timber-line as you North Islanders call it - the snow-line as we call it down here.'
